Tuesday's football photos
Man Utd 3-0 West Ham: The home side, looking to close the gap on Chelsea to one point, host West Ham and Antonio Valencia has an early chance for the hosts, but can only manage an embarrassing air shot
Man Utd striker Dimitar Berbatov goes for an early 50-50 ball with Hammers goalkeeper Rob Green. The Bulgarian is within his rights to do so, and Green emerges from the encounter unscathed
Brazilian midfielder Anderson is consoled by Hammers boss Gianfranco Zola after twisting his knee after just 10 minutes of play. He is replaced by South Korean Ji-Sung Park
The free-scoring Wayne Rooney notches his 26th goal of the season and gives the hosts the lead after a splendid move involving Park, Berbatov and Valencia, who provides the final, killer ball
Valencia is the provider again as he sets up Rooney for his 27th goal of the season and his 19th in 19 games. Four minutes later, he very nearly notches his hat-trick from the tightest of angles England's man of the moment Rooney is replaced by England's forgotten man Michael Owen and the 30-year-old gives his side a 3-0 lead with 10 minutes remaining Zola looks shellshocked after watching his side get ploughed into the Old Trafford turf by the indefatigable Rooney. The Hammers remain just four points above the relegation zone Stuttgart 1-1 Barcelona: It's the first leg of the last 16 clash between Stuttgart and Barcelona at the Mercedes-Benz Arena, and Brazilian striker Cacau gives the home side the lead after 25 minutes
Stuttgart's lead lasts until seven minutes after the restart, when $99m man Zlatan Ibrahimovic works an opening with Gerard Pique before equalising for the visitors
